Check google api(login per edit pagina e youtube, maps)
Youtube api(upload video)


Vincoli:
	-No google maps, si openStreetMaps
	-Usare OpenLocationCode
	-Usare server node.js
	-Usare mongoDB come database

Consegne:
	-Una città sola(Min 50 clip in 20 locations)
	-Clip:
		*What -> 15 sec max, def of location
		*How -> 15-30 sec max, general info(prices, opening hours, etc.)
		*Why -> I)15 sec max, reasons to visit
			II)
			III)
			.
			.
			more infos and curiosities


Facoltativo(Browser):
	-Directions to the place if not already there (10 pt.)
	-BOH...
	-Custom directions based on multiple POI with their clips pre loaded (10 pt.)
	-Ranking for bloggers, clips and routes (10 pt.)
	-If GPS not available user can navigate giving input of actual position:
		*Via
		*Città
		*Civico
		*Provincia
		*Paese 
		(5 pt.)
	-Clip filters based on metadata(language, date, length, audience, etc.) (5 pt.)
	-Turist location filters based on opening hours and type of location (5 pt.)
	-Option to check location as visited (5 pt.)
	-Show content of DBPedia of the location and language requested by user and reproduced with speech synthesis (20 pt.)
	-Ratings of each clip and location with feedback visualisation on map (10 pt.)

Facoltativo (Editor):
	-Clip editing (resizing of clip, merging of multiple clips, volume modulation, etc.) (20 pt.)
	-Uploading multiple clips with a single upload on YouTube (the browser must be able to view them separately) (20 pt.)
	-List of feedback of users on your clip and views statistics (5 pt.)
